      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## DORA Metrics \u2014 what this board shows & how to read it\nThe four [DORA](https://dora.dev/) software-delivery metrics for the microservices, computed **engine-neutrally**: the anchor is **ArgoCD** (`argocd_app_*`), which deploys the apps *whatever* CI engine (`jenkins` / `tekton` / `githubactions` / `argoworkflows`) built the image \u2014 so this board keeps working when `ci.engine` flips. Per-engine CI metrics only *enrich* lead time. Signal plumbing + methodology: [`docs/301 \u00a7 DORA`](../docs/301-OBSERVABILITY.md). Every metric here is a **proxy** \u2014 each one is labelled with its exact definition (and its exact PromQL lives in the panel descriptions), so read this box once before trusting the numbers.\n\n**Time range is part of the metric.** DORA is a *weeks* discipline \u2014 the board defaults to **7d** and the four headline stats are **range-scoped** (`$__range`): change the picker and they recompute. Two lifecycle caveats: **(1)** this platform's clusters are throwaway (`Decom`+`Day1`, [`docs/104`](../docs/104-REBUILD_SAFETY.md)) \u2014 ArgoCD's counters reset on rebuild (`increase()` tolerates the reset itself, you lose no in-window data), but pre-rebuild history only exists where the metrics backend **outlives the cluster** (grafana-cloud / managed-*; in oss the history dies with the Prometheus PVC). **(2)** A freshly-built cluster has *hours* of history \u2014 the stats are honest but not yet meaningful.\n\n### Dashboard sections at a glance\n| Section | What it answers |\n|---|---|\n| **Four headline stats** | The DORA scorecard for the selected range, colored by performance band (green = elite/high) |\n| **Deployments per day (+ by application)** | Cadence trend; whether both apps deploy or one dominates |\n| **Lead time trend** | Is merge\u2192running getting slower? p50 vs p95 divergence = flaky/slow tail |\n| **Sync outcomes by phase** | The raw material of CFR: Succeeded vs Failed/Error syncs per day |\n| **CI run failure rate** | The *build-side* failure ratio, to tell \"bad change\" from \"bad deploy\" |\n| **App health over time + Applications now** | Restore-time drill-down: when, how long, and which app left `Healthy` |\n\n### The four metrics \u2014 canonical definition vs this board's proxy\n| DORA metric | Canonical | Proxy here | Trust boundary |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Deployment frequency** | How often code reaches production | `argocd_app_sync_total{phase=\"Succeeded\", name=~\"microservices-.*\"}` increases | **Upper bound** \u2014 auto-sync also fires on drift *self-heal*, not only image bumps. Cross-check against the gitops-config repo's tag-bump commits when precision matters |\n| **Lead time for changes** | Commit \u2192 running in production | The **active engine's** run duration: Jenkins `ci_pipeline_run_duration_seconds` / Tekton `\u2026pipelinerun_duration_seconds` (p50/p95), Argo WF mean template runtime \u2014 their pipelines *include* the GitOps push **and** `argocd app wait`, so run duration \u2248 merge\u2192running | **GitHub Actions gap**: ARC runs execute in GitHub's plane, no in-cluster duration series \u2014 use the repo's Actions insights for that engine |\n| **Change failure rate** | % of deploys causing a failure in production | Failed syncs \u00f7 all syncs (headline) + the per-engine CI failure ratio (panel) | Not incident-correlated (no incident system in this PoC): a sync that *applied* but degraded the app shows in **restore time**, not here |\n| **Time to restore** | How long to recover from a production failure | Minutes (in range) where any `microservices-*` app reports `health_status != \"Healthy\"` (`argocd_app_info`) | Health-model MTTR, not paging MTTR: `Progressing` during a normal rollout also counts \u2014 read it together with the health timeline |\n\n### DORA performance bands (stat thresholds follow these)\n| Band | Deploy frequency | Lead time | CFR | Time to restore |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Elite** | on demand (multiple/day) | < 1 day | 0\u201315% | < 1 hour |\n| **High** | day\u2013week | 1 day\u20131 week | 16\u201330% | < 1 day |\n| **Medium/Low** | slower | slower | higher | longer |\n\n### How to read the results\n- \ud83d\udfe2 **Newcomer** \u2014 the four stat tiles are the scorecard: **green = elite/high** band for that metric over the selected range. All green on a demo cluster mostly proves the *pipeline* is healthy; the numbers get meaningful as the range grows.\n- \ud83d\udfe1 **Operator** \u2014 trends beat snapshots: rising *deploys/day* with flat *CFR* is healthy scaling; a *lead-time p95* drifting away from p50 means a slow/flaky tail (find the culprit run in the active engine's CI board); `Failed`/`Error` bars in *sync outcomes* that cluster in time usually mean one bad change retried, not many bad changes.\n- \ud83d\udd35 **Specialist** \u2014 investigation recipes: **CFR spike** \u2192 *Sync outcomes by phase* for the day, then the app's History in the ArgoCD UI (`argocd.<domain>`) for the failing revision; **lead-time regression** \u2192 the active engine's overview board (`CI-CD / Jenkins Controller` \u00b7 `Tekton CI` \u00b7 `GitHub Actions CI` \u00b7 `Argo Workflows CI`) for the stage-level split, and `CI-CD / JVM Internals` if the build JVMs are the suspect; **restore episode** \u2192 *App health over time* for the window, then `CI-CD / Microservices Overview` (RED) + `CI-CD / PostgreSQL` for the blast radius \u2014 remember `Progressing` \u2260 outage; **self-heal inflation check** \u2192 compare *deploys/day* against actual image-tag commits in the gitops-config repo; a large gap = drift self-heals, worth investigating *why* there is drift.\n\n> **Empty panels are not faults**: no syncs/runs in the selected range (fresh cluster, idle day, or the engine's gap documented above) \u2014 widen the range or trigger a pipeline. This board ships in **all four** `observability.mode` backends and is surfaced automatically on the **Backstage** platform component's Monitoring tab (oss / grafana-cloud)."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Deployment frequency \u2014 successful syncs (range)",
      "description": "sum(increase(argocd_app_sync_total{name=~\"microservices-.*\", phase=\"Succeeded\"}[$__range])). Upper bound: includes self-heal re-syncs.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 23
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(increase(argocd_app_sync_total{name=~\"microservices-.*\", phase=\"Succeeded\"}[$__range])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "deploys",
          "instant": true
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "decimals": 0,
          "color": {
            "mode": "fixed",
            "fixedColor": "blue"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "graphMode": "none",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "textMode": "auto"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Lead time p50 \u2014 CI run duration (active engine)",
      "description": "Jenkins/Tekton: p50 of the pipeline-run duration histogram over the range (their pipelines include the GitOps push + argocd wait). Argo Workflows: mean template runtime. GitHub Actions: no in-cluster series (documented gap). Only the ACTIVE engine returns data.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 6,
        "y": 23
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(ci_pipeline_run_duration_seconds_bucket[$__range])))",
          "legendFormat": "Jenkins p50",
          "instant": true
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(tekton_pipelines_controller_pipelinerun_duration_seconds_bucket{status=\"success\"}[$__range])))",
          "legendFormat": "Tekton p50",
          "instant": true
        },
        {
          "refId": "C",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "sum(rate(argo_workflows_workflowtemplate_runtime_sum[$__range])) / clamp_min(sum(rate(argo_workflows_workflowtemplate_runtime_count[$__range])), 0.000001)",
          "legendFormat": "Argo WF mean",
          "instant": true
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "decimals": 1,
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 900
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 3600
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "graphMode": "none",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "textMode": "value_and_name"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Change failure rate \u2014 failed syncs (range)",
      "description": "100 \u00d7 failed syncs (phase Error|Failed) \u00f7 all syncs of the microservices apps. DORA bands: elite/high \u2264 15%.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 23
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "100 * (sum(increase(argocd_app_sync_total{name=~\"microservices-.*\", phase=~\"Error|Failed\"}[$__range])) or vector(0)) / clamp_min((sum(increase(argocd_app_sync_total{name=~\"microservices-.*\"}[$__range])) or vector(0)), 1)",
          "legendFormat": "CFR",
          "instant": true
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percent",
          "decimals": 1,
          "min": 0,
          "max": 100,
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
